OL,3,CFamily of aid worker killed in Gaza
OL,4,Ccall for independent inquiry
OL,6,FSpeaking ahead of the service, his
OL,7,Fcousin Louise Kirby described how the
OL,8,Ffamily had been "touched" to receive
OL,9,Fpersonal letters of condolence from
OL,10,Fthe King and Queen, and former foreign
OL,11,Fsecretary Lord Cameron.
OL,13,FShe said: "The murder of James and his
OL,14,Ffellow aid workers, for whom clearance
OL,15,Fhad been given for their humanitarian
OL,16,Fwork, is a diabolical tragedy.
OL,18,F"Whilst we have had much support, we
OL,19,Fare still struggling to find answers
OL,20,Fand accountability for what happened.
OL,26,@pD@QOUpD@YO]uD@KOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
